pattern.primary_approach:

Windows-MCP:Powershell-Tool({
    command: "Get-ChildItem -Path '$project_root' -Recurse -Include '*.java' | 
             Select-String -Pattern '@(RestController|Service|Repository|Configuration|Component)' | 
             Group-Object Pattern | 
             Select-Object Name, Count"
})

pattern.mapping:
@RestController ‚Üí Actor entity
@Service ‚Üí Process entity
@Repository ‚Üí Resource entity
@Configuration ‚Üí Context entity
@Component ‚Üí Determine by analysis

pattern.primary_approach:

Windows-MCP:Powershell-Tool({
    command: "Get-ChildItem -Path '$project_root' -Recurse -Include '*.java' | 
             Select-String -Pattern '@(GetMapping|PostMapping|PutMapping|DeleteMapping)' | 
             ForEach-Object {
                 [PSCustomObject]@{
                     File = (Split-Path $_.Path -Leaf)
                     Line = $_.LineNumber
                     Method = ($_.Line -replace '.*@(\\w+).*','$1')
                     Path = if($_.Line -match '\"([^\"]+)\"') {$matches[1]} else {''}
                 }
             }"
})


Windows-MCP:Powershell-Tool({
    command: "Get-ChildItem -Path '$project_root' -Recurse -Include '*Repository.java' | 
             ForEach-Object {
                 $content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw
                 [PSCustomObject]@{
                     File = $_.Name
                     HasEntityGraph = ($content -match '@EntityGraph')
                     HasCustomQuery = ($content -match '@Query')
                     HasRelationships = ($content -match '@(OneToMany|ManyToOne|ManyToMany)')
                 }
             }"
})


Windows-MCP:Powershell-Tool({
    command: "Get-ChildItem -Path '$project_root' -Recurse -Include '*.java' | 
             Select-String -Pattern '@(EnableWebSecurity|PreAuthorize|Secured)' | 
             Select-Object Path, LineNumber, Line"
})


Windows-MCP:Powershell-Tool({
    command: "Get-ChildItem -Path '$project_root' -Recurse -Include '*.java' | 
             Select-String -Pattern '@Transactional' | 
             ForEach-Object {
                 [PSCustomObject]@{
                     File = (Split-Path $_.Path -Leaf)
                     Line = $_.LineNumber
                     ReadOnly = ($_.Line -match 'readOnly\\s*=\\s*true')
                     OnClass = ($_.Line -match 'class')
                 }
             }"
})

NEO4J_CRITICAL_RULES.indexes:
Create BEFORE any graph operations (performance critical):
CYPHER 25 CREATE INDEX nav_namespace IF NOT EXISTS FOR (n:NavigationMaster) ON (n.namespace);
CYPHER 25 CREATE INDEX entity_code IF NOT EXISTS FOR (e:SystemEntity) ON (e.code);
CYPHER 25 CREATE INDEX detail_path IF NOT EXISTS FOR (d:EntityDetail) ON (d.file_path);
CYPHER 25 CREATE INDEX detail_issue IF NOT EXISTS FOR (d:EntityDetail) ON (d.has_issue);
Benefit: O(1) lookups, 100x faster queries
**NEW**: IF index creation fails: - Log warning - Continue without indexes (queries will be slower but functional) - Don't halt entire process for index failures
